questions.DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I:
The Welcoming Ceremony is one of the most important annual events of the Chinese Global Community. The purpose of this event is to reunite the returning students and welcome the new students to our campus, as well as help the international students to integrate into the UCSD community. 
Specifically, the “CGC Opening Ceremony” is a grand opening ceremony that primarily features stage performances. This celebration marks the commencement of the new academic year, showcasing a variety of artistic expressions through dance, drama, and music performances, reflecting the cultural diversity and creative talents within the academic community. Our goal for this opening ceremony is not only to let new students know how CGC could help them in their future University life but also to create a sense of belonging to them in this brand-new life. In addition, we are committed to helping new students get a quicker understanding of the facilities and the various departments available to them, and we will introduce UCSD to students at this opening ceremony so that they will not be unfamiliar with the campus. We also organize audience interactions so that new students can make friends from the moment they arrive and not be alone. This event is open to every single student (including newly admitted, transferring, and current students) and every staff member in the UC San Diego community. We hope that this event will serve as a mobilization for the start of the new academic year, encouraging students and staff to work together and enjoy their new academic life.

questions.DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: This will be VGDC's first event of the 2024 school year in which we will be introducing the club to incoming students and those interested in game development. The event will go over what exactly game development entails and the many disciplines such as art, programming, audio, and writing that it includes -- emphasizing that game development is a field where anyone from any major/study can contribute and participate in no matter the skill level. questions.DESCRIBE THE EVENT, TRY TO INCLUDE HOW I: The "Majiang at UC San Diego Halloween Social Night" is a free and opening to all event planned by the Mjiang at UC San Diego. The event is planned to be held on October 31, 2024, and will be offering a highly interactive social bonding event to all students and staff at UCSD. An estimated 300 participants are expected for this party event. We are aiming to provide food and beverages and also host various forms of performances throughout the night for students to relax after the first round of midterms and enjoy the Halloween spirit. Members of the Majiang club will also be providing interactive games with scripted plots, and surprise gifts to further entertain the community. We are hoping this event will be a memorable night for students to get to know more about the Majiang members and a chance for them to meet one another and bond with more individuals in the larger San Diego community.
